                    <figure corresp="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IreneVagionakis/PPRET/main/webapps/ROOT/content/images/Bernier.jpg"></figure>
                    <p>I studied ancient history at the University of Parma, where I obtained a MA (2013) and a PhD (2017) with a dissertation on the legislation of the emperor Valentinian I. In 2017/2018 I held a fellowship at the Istituto Italiano per gli Studi Storici Benedetto Croce (Napoli) and in 2020 I was granted a DAAD scholarship for a research period at the University of Tübingen. My researches have focused on the administrative system of the later Roman empire, on the ancient law codes as sources for the history of 4th and 5th Centuries and on the agrarian history of late and post-Roman Europe.</p>
